// runtime/sfn/memory/arena.sfn
//
// First Sailfin-native runtime module shipped into the
// `build/native/sailfin` binary alongside the C arena. M2.1
// proof-of-life per `docs/runtime_architecture.md` §2.1.1 and
// issue #394 (epic #389).
//
// Status: stub bodies that delegate to libc `malloc` / `free` /
// `realloc`. M3 replaces the bodies with a real page-chain bump
// allocator (architect plan in #389 M2.2 / `runtime_architecture.md`
// §2.1.1). Until then this module exists to prove the new
// runtime/sfn/* link path:
//
//   - `runtime/sfn/memory/arena.sfn` compiles to a `.o` and
//     links into the compiler binary via
//     `_compile_runtime_sfn_sources` in
//     `compiler/src/cli_main.sfn:521`. Historically (before
//     Stage E PR7 / #383) the prior `scripts/build.sh`'s
//     `RUNTIME_SFN_ALLOW` allowlist was a second source of truth
//     kept in lockstep with `runtime/native/capsule.toml`'s
//     `sfn-sources`; with build.sh retired, the manifest is the
//     sole list.
//   - The Sailfin-emitted `sfn_arena_sfn_*` symbol family
//     coexists with the C arena's matching `sfn_arena_*` exports
//     (no link-time collision). Both arenas are linked into
//     every compiler binary; the C arena remains the production
//     allocator until M3 retires `runtime/native/src/sailfin_arena.c`.
//
// Naming: the `_sfn_` infix distinguishes this module's exports
// from the C arena's API (`sfn_arena_create` vs.
// `sfn_arena_sfn_create`). Both name families share the
// `sfn_arena*` prefix so the issue's `nm | grep sfn_arena`
// audit matches both, while `nm | grep sfn_arena_sfn_` is
// the specific marker that proves THIS module shipped (and is
// the assertion in `compiler/tests/e2e/test_runtime_sfn_sources_active.sh`).
//
// At M3 the cutover plan flips the C arena's `sfn_arena_*`
// symbols to `static` (file-local) and replaces the bodies here
// with the real page-chain implementation; a thin C trampoline
// then bridges legacy callers. That migration is one PR with a
// single rollback path because the namespace is already stable.
//
// Effects: none. Memory primitives live below the I/O layer
// (same discipline as `runtime/sfn/platform/libc.sfn`). The
// `![io]` / `![clock]` annotations attach to *adapters* that
// wrap these primitives, never to the primitives themselves.
//
// Why not `import { malloc, free, realloc } from
// "../platform/libc"`? The seed compiler shipped with this PR
// (0.5.10-alpha.8) predates the typechecker's `float` accept-
// list relaxation (HEAD's `compiler/src/typecheck_types.sfn:618`)
// and rejects `runtime/sfn/platform/libc.sfn`'s
// `sailfin_runtime_sleep(milliseconds: float)` declaration with
// E0805 the moment any module imports from that file. Inlining
// the three libc declarations we need keeps this module
// self-contained for the seed's typechecker. Once the seed
// catches up post-merge, a follow-up PR can flip these to a
// cross-module import without touching the bodies.
extern fn malloc(size: usize) -> * u8;

extern fn free(ptr: * u8) -> void;

extern fn realloc(ptr: * u8, new_size: usize) -> * u8;

// `sfn_arena_sfn_create(default_page_size)` returns an opaque
// arena handle. M2.1 stub allocates a single libc heap block of
// the requested size; M3 replaces this with a real ArenaPage
// chain per `runtime_architecture.md` §2.1.1.
//
// `default_page_size = 0` is documented in §2.1.1 as "use the
// implementation default" — the M0.5 C arena picks 1 MiB. The
// stub forwards the literal request to `malloc`; ISO C lets
// `malloc(0)` return either `NULL` or a unique pointer that
// `free` will accept, so callers must treat a `0`-byte request
// as undefined-payload (the proof-of-life probe never reads
// from the returned pointer). The size policy is irrelevant
// until M3 lands the real allocator.
fn sfn_arena_sfn_create(default_page_size: usize) -> * u8 {
    return malloc(default_page_size);
}

// `sfn_arena_sfn_alloc(arena, size, align)` is the bump
// allocation primitive. M2.1 stub forwards `size` to `malloc`
// and ignores `arena` / `align` — the real page-chain version
// (M3) honors `align` via the `_align_up` helper from
// `runtime/native/src/sailfin_arena.c:19`. Per the v0 C-ABI
// accept-list, `align` rides as `usize`.
fn sfn_arena_sfn_alloc(arena: * u8, size: usize, align: usize) -> * u8 {
    return malloc(size);
}

// `sfn_arena_sfn_reset(arena)` resets all pages to `used = 0`
// without freeing backing memory. M2.1 stub is a no-op because
// the libc-backed allocator owns no per-allocation metadata to
// reset. M3 walks the page list per `sailfin_arena.c:80`.
fn sfn_arena_sfn_reset(arena: * u8) -> void { }

// `sfn_arena_sfn_destroy(arena)` releases the arena and every
// backing page. M2.1 stub forwards to libc `free`; M3 walks the
// page list and frees each page before the arena struct itself
// (`sailfin_arena.c:126`).
fn sfn_arena_sfn_destroy(arena: * u8) -> void { free(arena); }

// `sfn_arena_sfn_realloc(arena, ptr, old_size, new_size, align)`
// is the grow-if-at-tip realloc optimized for the
// `string_append` hot path (`runtime_architecture.md` §2.1.1).
// M2.1 stub delegates to libc `realloc` — `old_size` and
// `align` are unused at this stage. M3 implements the real
// tip-grow logic (`sailfin_arena.c:208`).
fn sfn_arena_sfn_realloc(arena: * u8, ptr: * u8, old_size: usize, new_size: usize, align: usize) -> * u8 {
    return realloc(ptr, new_size);
}
